<p>I have website <code>www.domain.com</code> (on server root is in <code>/domain.com/web/</code>), now I created subdomain <code>m.domain.com</code> (on server root is in <code>/domain.com/sub/m/</code>).</p>  <p>I added .htaccess to subdomain root:</p>  <pre><code>RewriteEngine on RewriteBase /  RewriteCond %{HTTP_HOST} ^(www\.)?m\.domain\.com$ RewriteCond %{REQUEST_URI} !^/m RewriteRule ^(.*)$ ../../web/$1 [QSA,L] </code></pre>  <p>But it is showing <code>Internal Server Error</code>.</p>  <p>I tried this:</p>  <pre><code>RewriteRule ^(.*)$ http://www.domain.com/$1 [QSA,L] </code></pre>  <p>But that will redirect you to the main domain. I need to stay on subdomain, but have the same content as on main domain.</p>  <p>Also I have checked more solutions here on SO, but none of them is working.</p>  <p><strong>EDIT:</strong></p>  <p>I tried in Apache to set up another VirtualHost:</p>  <pre><code>DocumentRoot /domain.com/web &lt;Directory "/domain.com/web"&gt; allow from all Options None &lt;/Directory&gt; ServerName m.domain.com ServerAlias m.domain.com </code></pre>  <p>Now also main domain and also subdomain shows 503 - Forbidden.</p>